cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely category as the paper presents a visual-inertial simultaneous localization and mapping (SLAM) system, which is a common topic in robotics research.
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is also likely as the paper involves processing visual data from cameras to estimate camera pose and map the environment.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is a possible category as the paper may involve machine learning techniques for loop-closing and non-linear optimization.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also possible as the paper may involve AI techniques for relocalization and continued SLAM operation.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is less likely but still possible as the paper involves developing a real-time capable system for visual-inertial SLAM.
